cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.ME 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on simulating granular materials for robotic tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the authors use depth images of granular formations to infer material properties. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the authors use likelihood-free Bayesian inference to estimate material properties. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses a software and hardware framework for calibrating a physics simulator. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is relevant as the paper deals with the simulation of granular materials, which is a topic of interest in mechanical engineering.
